1
00:00:07,945 --> 00:00:09,864
[somber music playing]

2
00:00:09,947 --> 00:00:12,158
[So-yeon breathes deeply]

3
00:00:23,335 --> 00:00:24,170
Hello.

4
00:00:24,253 --> 00:00:26,505
[tense music playing]

5
00:00:29,383 --> 00:00:30,718
You watched the surveillance cam?

6
00:00:30,801 --> 00:00:32,636
Not yet. I… I'll check it.

7
00:00:35,765 --> 00:00:37,266
[camera clicking]

8
00:00:40,227 --> 00:00:41,645
[Woo-jin] All four dressed the same.

9
00:00:42,521 --> 00:00:47,234
All in black jackets, black pants,
and black masks on their faces.

10
00:00:47,735 --> 00:00:49,195
And they were all huge.

11
00:00:49,278 --> 00:00:52,198
What do you mean when you say huge?
How big were they?

12
00:00:52,281 --> 00:00:55,993
All four of them seemed to be
much bigger than both of us, for sure.

13
00:00:56,077 --> 00:01:00,331
And two of them
could easily have been 6'2", or taller.

14
00:01:01,165 --> 00:01:03,167
They all looked like
they worked out a lot.

15
00:01:03,876 --> 00:01:05,586
And some knew karate.

16
00:01:06,087 --> 00:01:08,964
And they had big batons
which had Tasers on them.

17
00:01:10,674 --> 00:01:14,178
Also, they had shoe covers on their feet.

18
00:01:15,012 --> 00:01:17,473
Otherwise, have you noticed
anything out of the ordinary?

19
00:01:18,432 --> 00:01:19,391
[Woo-jin] Actually…

20
00:01:21,519 --> 00:01:22,895
Mm. Go for it.

21
00:01:24,146 --> 00:01:27,900
You see, some strangers came to our place
three days ago.

22
00:01:27,983 --> 00:01:31,654
They were like, Gun-woo had to join
this professional boxing league they have.

23
00:01:31,737 --> 00:01:34,281
IKFC was the name of the league.

24
00:01:34,365 --> 00:01:38,285
It was a threat, not an invitation.
Those two men were massive.

25
00:01:38,369 --> 00:01:40,788
They even brought us
a billion won to sign.

26
00:01:40,871 --> 00:01:41,914
A billion?

27
00:01:42,915 --> 00:01:44,166
They brought it.

28
00:01:45,376 --> 00:01:47,920
So you believe this case
is related to that?

29
00:01:48,003 --> 00:01:50,673
I do, and I think they'd visit us again.

30
00:01:51,674 --> 00:01:54,510
I checked the security footage
and there's nothing suspicious.

31
00:01:54,593 --> 00:01:55,678
Huh?

32
00:01:56,387 --> 00:01:58,389
Just a few days ago we hooked that up.

33
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:01,225
You shouldn't listen to our conversation.

34
00:02:02,393 --> 00:02:03,853
Yeah, well, I could hear you.

35
00:02:03,936 --> 00:02:05,646
You were pretty loud.

36
00:02:07,982 --> 00:02:09,775
[detective 1] Sorry about that.
[clears throat]

37
00:02:10,734 --> 00:02:13,863
Anyway, the screen doesn't show anything,
and the time doesn't pause at all.

38
00:02:15,239 --> 00:02:16,657
[detective 2] Thanks. You can leave.

39
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,326
Anything else to share?

40
00:02:22,246 --> 00:02:25,040
Oh yeah. He fought
in the WBC Championship last week.

41
00:02:25,124 --> 00:02:28,377
-His opponent was--
-Oh yeah. The boxer. I knew it.

42
00:02:30,171 --> 00:02:32,464
-Uh… yeah.
-Wow!

43
00:02:32,548 --> 00:02:33,757
-I'm honored.
-Thanks.

44
00:02:35,342 --> 00:02:37,386
I used to be a boxer when I was younger.

45
00:02:38,012 --> 00:02:40,639
I watched your fight
probably three times. [chuckles]

46
00:02:41,140 --> 00:02:42,850
Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.

47
00:02:43,726 --> 00:02:45,144
Okay then, please go on.

48
00:02:45,728 --> 00:02:48,022
I read that the other fighter
has gone missing.

49
00:02:48,105 --> 00:02:51,233
That's weird, don't you think?
So that might be linked.

50
00:02:53,527 --> 00:02:54,695
That'll do for now.

51
00:02:55,196 --> 00:02:57,948
Me and the team
will start investigating right away.

52
00:02:59,617 --> 00:03:03,579
Your house could be dangerous right now,
so consider moving to another place.

53
00:03:07,917 --> 00:03:11,712
Tell me, in your expert opinion,
is a hotel safe enough for us?

54
00:03:12,296 --> 00:03:14,465
Avoid unknown people and places.

55
00:03:15,716 --> 00:03:17,968
[sighs] Where should we go then?

56
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,557
Tae-yeong's?

57
00:03:28,103 --> 00:03:29,605
[tense music continues]

58
00:03:40,449 --> 00:03:41,533
Hey, officer.

59
00:03:42,576 --> 00:03:44,078
-How's it going?
-[man 1] Hello.

60
00:03:44,161 --> 00:03:45,829
-Hello.
-[man 2] Hello, detective.

61
00:03:46,705 --> 00:03:48,582
Right here is where the fire began.

62
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:52,294
You see that melted gasoline container?
An improvised explosive device.

63
00:03:52,962 --> 00:03:55,673
The detonator was likely triggered
by a cell phone signal.

64
00:03:56,632 --> 00:04:01,762
Hmm. And, uh, how knowledgeable
does someone have to be to make this?

65
00:04:01,845 --> 00:04:05,933
Hmm, a high-level EOD tech
should be able to do this.

66
00:04:08,852 --> 00:04:11,563
-Also, we found a wallet in the car.
-Oh!

67
00:04:22,741 --> 00:04:23,575
You have a…

68
00:04:23,659 --> 00:04:25,119
-[man 2] Right here, detective.
-Ah.

69
00:04:33,544 --> 00:04:36,922
PEOPLE GUARD SECURITY
MANAGER / BODYGUARD SON JIN-NAM

70
00:04:40,968 --> 00:04:42,970
[tense electronic music playing]

71
00:05:08,871 --> 00:05:11,457
BLOODHOUNDS 2

72
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:12,458
[music fades]

73
00:05:17,338 --> 00:05:19,340
[gentle music playing]

74
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:23,469
-[Gun-woo] Thank you.
-[officer] Of course.

75
00:05:32,644 --> 00:05:34,021
Hey, Ma.

76
00:05:36,815 --> 00:05:37,733
Are you okay?

77
00:05:39,318 --> 00:05:40,277
[So-yeon] I'm fine.

78
00:05:40,778 --> 00:05:43,739
I'm okay if both of you boys are okay.

79
00:05:44,406 --> 00:05:45,741
We're okay for now, Mom.

80
00:05:46,408 --> 00:05:49,495
They told us
two more days for new windows.

81
00:05:49,578 --> 00:05:52,539
That's fine. We can do this.

82
00:05:53,082 --> 00:05:55,334
We must stick together
through all of this.

83
00:05:55,834 --> 00:05:56,710
[Gun-woo] Mm.

84
00:06:00,089 --> 00:06:02,132
[tense music playing]

85
00:06:02,716 --> 00:06:03,967
They're moving.

86
00:06:05,761 --> 00:06:06,762
Take a right.

87
00:06:16,438 --> 00:06:17,898
You sure they're coming here?

88
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,442
Yeah.

89
00:06:45,717 --> 00:06:47,052
-[clamoring]
-[music fades]

90
00:06:53,142 --> 00:06:55,185
[ominous music playing]

91
00:06:57,146 --> 00:06:58,439
[sighs]

92
00:07:01,650 --> 00:07:02,776
[sighs]

93
00:07:11,577 --> 00:07:14,288
[groaning]

94
00:07:20,002 --> 00:07:21,044
[man 1] 2196!

95
00:07:21,545 --> 00:07:23,338
-2196!
-[man 2] We need help over here!

96
00:07:23,422 --> 00:07:26,467
-[man 1] 2196! Hey, hey!
-[man 2] It's an emergency!

97
00:07:26,550 --> 00:07:28,552
[music intensifies]

98
00:07:38,312 --> 00:07:41,064
-[man 3] How long has he been unconscious?
-[man 1] About ten minutes.

99
00:07:41,148 --> 00:07:41,982
[man 3] Got it.

100
00:07:46,862 --> 00:07:52,075
-[engine starts]
-[siren wailing]

101
00:08:09,426 --> 00:08:11,887
Why stop here? This place is abandoned.

102
00:08:13,472 --> 00:08:14,681
[groans]

103
00:08:14,765 --> 00:08:16,767
[gags, wheezes]

104
00:08:17,601 --> 00:08:18,727
[blows thudding]

105
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:22,189
[guard groans, yells in pain]

106
00:08:31,365 --> 00:08:32,741
[groans]

107
00:08:32,824 --> 00:08:33,909
[grunts]

108
00:08:33,992 --> 00:08:35,410
Ow! Shit!

109
00:08:46,088 --> 00:08:47,047
[music fades]

110
00:08:49,758 --> 00:08:52,719
[doorbell chiming]

111
00:08:53,762 --> 00:08:55,055
Just a minute!

112
00:08:55,806 --> 00:08:57,683
[gentle music playing]

113
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:11,488
-Well, hello! Welcome.
-Tae-yeong.

114
00:09:12,114 --> 00:09:14,366
This way. Careful. Welcome.

115
00:09:15,158 --> 00:09:16,159
[Tae-yeong chuckles]

116
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,078
I'm sorry to intrude.

117
00:09:18,161 --> 00:09:21,999
Don't feel bad. I think of all those
wonderful dishes you prepared for me.

118
00:09:22,082 --> 00:09:23,750
-This is my honor.
-[exhales]

119
00:09:23,834 --> 00:09:26,336
I'm just glad that I can be of assistance.

120
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:29,715
Sorry about the short notice.
Thank you. Really.

121
00:09:30,299 --> 00:09:32,092
It's nothing. My pleasure.

122
00:09:33,260 --> 00:09:36,680
So you both can stay in this room.
I'll get you some blankets.

123
00:09:36,763 --> 00:09:38,015
Ms. Yoon, follow me.

124
00:09:42,436 --> 00:09:43,645
And this will be your room.

125
00:09:43,729 --> 00:09:47,899
My sister is in the States right now,
and she's almost never here.

126
00:09:48,442 --> 00:09:49,484
It's perfect.

127
00:09:49,985 --> 00:09:52,070
-[Woo-jin] Tae-yeong.
-Coming!

128
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,036
[So-yeon exhales]

129
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:09,921
I need a favor from you.

130
00:10:11,089 --> 00:10:12,841
Can you help me with some research?

131
00:10:14,009 --> 00:10:14,843
Yeah.

132
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:18,597
NO RESULTS FOUND FOR "IKFC"

133
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,515
[tense music playing]

134
00:10:31,943 --> 00:10:34,196
[music intensifies]

135
00:10:37,407 --> 00:10:38,742
NO RESULTS FOUND FOR "IKFC"

136
00:10:42,788 --> 00:10:44,289
The dark web will know.

137
00:10:45,165 --> 00:10:47,334
Dark web? What's that?

138
00:10:47,417 --> 00:10:48,543
It's, uh…

139
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:52,130
The internet we know
is just the tip of the iceberg,

140
00:10:52,214 --> 00:10:55,717
and far beneath that surface
is what is known as the dark web.

141
00:10:55,801 --> 00:10:57,969
On the dark web, everyone is anonymous,

142
00:10:58,053 --> 00:11:01,139
and criminals gather there
and take advantage of that anonymity.

143
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:04,643
So, um, I'm not sure what you mean.
How can you stay anonymous?

144
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:09,523
Uh, so when we're online,
we leave an IP address behind,

145
00:11:09,606 --> 00:11:11,358
which is digital proof.

146
00:11:11,441 --> 00:11:12,567
When crimes occur online,

147
00:11:12,651 --> 00:11:15,529
we can track the IP address
to figure out the criminal's identity.

148
00:11:15,612 --> 00:11:18,365
See, on the dark web,
the IP address is encrypted,

149
00:11:18,448 --> 00:11:19,658
and that's difficult to undo,

150
00:11:19,741 --> 00:11:21,785
so it's nearly impossible
to track the user.

151
00:11:21,868 --> 00:11:24,287
Criminals take advantage
and form a black market,

152
00:11:24,371 --> 00:11:26,873
using Bitcoin to make their transactions.

153
00:11:26,957 --> 00:11:29,710
Whoa. So much information.

154
00:11:29,793 --> 00:11:32,587
Uh… [chuckles]

155
00:11:32,671 --> 00:11:35,590
When we first met,
I worked the cyber investigation unit,

156
00:11:35,674 --> 00:11:38,135
searching for these dark websites
so we can shut them down.

157
00:11:38,218 --> 00:11:40,971
These sites I killed
ran a variety of illegal businesses.

158
00:11:41,054 --> 00:11:44,599
There were some smuggling drugs,
selling IEDs and poisonous substances.

159
00:11:44,683 --> 00:11:46,685
And some sites offered murder for hire.

160
00:11:46,768 --> 00:11:50,772
What shocked me the most was that one site
offered options on how to murder someone.

161
00:11:50,856 --> 00:11:53,275
Options like how to torture,
which acids are better,

162
00:11:53,358 --> 00:11:55,360
staging a suicide, stuff like that.

163
00:11:56,778 --> 00:12:00,157
I still remember
the admin's handle. "M-A-N-J-I."

164
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:03,660
That's "manji," the spelling
of the Buddhist symbol "man" in English.

165
00:12:03,744 --> 00:12:04,870
Isn't that ironic?

166
00:12:04,953 --> 00:12:07,581
Someone who kills for money
using that name.

167
00:12:08,498 --> 00:12:11,251
So I'm guessing I'll have more luck there.

168
00:12:18,759 --> 00:12:19,593
[Tae-yeong exhales]

169
00:12:25,932 --> 00:12:27,100
Here we are.

170
00:12:27,184 --> 00:12:28,059
[music fades]

171
00:12:33,398 --> 00:12:34,816
[Woo-jin] IKFC.

172
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:38,153
[heavy metal music playing]

173
00:12:57,297 --> 00:12:59,007
How does the skin tear so easily?

174
00:13:10,435 --> 00:13:11,603
[music fades]

175
00:13:19,694 --> 00:13:20,654
What's the matter?

176
00:13:23,615 --> 00:13:24,741
[sighs]

177
00:13:25,325 --> 00:13:26,284
What? What?

178
00:13:26,368 --> 00:13:29,704
Uh, well, it requires a credit card,

179
00:13:29,788 --> 00:13:32,958
but you should never
enter your credit card on the dark web.

180
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:36,002
Anyone there might steal
and use that information.

181
00:13:36,086 --> 00:13:39,005
Do you think you can hack in,
or something like that?

182
00:13:39,089 --> 00:13:44,177
Oh. If I do that,
the admins of the site are able to see me,

183
00:13:44,261 --> 00:13:46,054
and if they're faster than me,

184
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,808
they can hack this computer
before I can break in here.

185
00:13:49,891 --> 00:13:53,562
They could plant a virus
and take full control of this computer.

186
00:13:54,062 --> 00:13:56,106
There are hackers here,
hanging out on the dark web,

187
00:13:56,189 --> 00:13:58,441
who far surpass all my skills.

188
00:13:58,942 --> 00:14:01,820
-Sorry about that.
-No. No worries. Huh.

189
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,155
[quiet intriguing music playing]

190
00:14:04,239 --> 00:14:05,115
[Gun-woo sighs]

191
00:14:05,699 --> 00:14:06,658
[sighs]

192
00:14:11,538 --> 00:14:14,124
So… we need a plan.

193
00:14:14,207 --> 00:14:15,834
Oh yeah. A plan.

194
00:14:18,086 --> 00:14:20,922
So we just have to avoid
using our own cards. Isn't that right?

195
00:14:22,299 --> 00:14:24,968
Oh, well, that'll work, for sure.

196
00:14:26,094 --> 00:14:27,137
[sighs]

197
00:14:31,141 --> 00:14:32,475
[exhales]

198
00:14:33,143 --> 00:14:34,019
Woo-jin…

199
00:14:38,857 --> 00:14:41,693
what if we ask our Marine superior?

200
00:14:42,193 --> 00:14:43,320
Mr. Moon Gwang-mu?

201
00:14:45,322 --> 00:14:48,783
Wait a minute. A mule card?
Is that what you're thinking?

202
00:14:52,245 --> 00:14:54,331
Mule cards are created
by stealing identities.

203
00:14:54,414 --> 00:14:57,250
Whoever owns the card
would definitely be in trouble.

204
00:14:58,001 --> 00:14:58,919
[music fades]

205
00:14:59,002 --> 00:15:00,128
What about a dead person?

206
00:15:00,754 --> 00:15:01,588
Uh,

207
00:15:02,297 --> 00:15:04,883
well, if you do that,

208
00:15:05,383 --> 00:15:06,843
then you can't tell me.

209
00:15:07,344 --> 00:15:08,178
Yeah.

210
00:15:14,059 --> 00:15:14,893
Hey.

211
00:15:15,518 --> 00:15:16,353
Yeah?

212
00:15:16,937 --> 00:15:20,190
I'm thinking you stay behind and take care
of Tae-yeong and your mother.

213
00:15:20,857 --> 00:15:23,360
-What? Why?
-[Woo-jin] Who knows what'll happen?

214
00:15:24,361 --> 00:15:27,489
Okay? I'll meet up
with our old Marine superior.

215
00:15:31,576 --> 00:15:32,786
Mm. I got it.

216
00:15:39,584 --> 00:15:40,460
[sighs]

217
00:15:40,543 --> 00:15:43,088
[quiet ominous music playing]

218
00:15:46,341 --> 00:15:47,509
He's moving now.

219
00:15:49,594 --> 00:15:51,262
Who? Gun-woo?

220
00:15:51,763 --> 00:15:53,556
[hacker] No. The other guy.

221
00:15:54,641 --> 00:15:56,434
[tires squeal]

222
00:16:04,025 --> 00:16:06,736
[tires squealing]

223
00:16:23,003 --> 00:16:23,962
[music fades]

224
00:16:24,546 --> 00:16:25,588
[gasps]

225
00:16:26,089 --> 00:16:30,552
[breathes shakily]

226
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:38,768
In-beom, hello.

227
00:16:39,310 --> 00:16:43,398
Hi. I'm responsible
for getting you out of prison.

228
00:16:44,357 --> 00:16:46,276
Thanks for accepting my offer.

229
00:16:46,359 --> 00:16:49,195
From now on,
we work together to kill Kim Gun-woo.

230
00:16:50,113 --> 00:16:51,823
[quiet ominous music playing]

231
00:16:55,618 --> 00:16:58,121
I'm confused. Didn't you accept the offer?

232
00:17:00,874 --> 00:17:02,208
[sighs]

233
00:17:06,629 --> 00:17:08,840
You're placing me in a tough position.

234
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:10,216
[exhales]

235
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:14,304
Hey.

236
00:17:14,387 --> 00:17:15,805
Listen carefully.

237
00:17:20,143 --> 00:17:23,146
There's absolutely nothing
within ten kilometers of here.

238
00:17:23,229 --> 00:17:26,691
So if you leave this place,
I'll call the police.

239
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:29,152
[snarls quietly]

240
00:17:29,235 --> 00:17:31,905
The police will likely show up
in ten minutes.

241
00:17:32,655 --> 00:17:34,157
You might be fast,

242
00:17:35,283 --> 00:17:37,744
but I doubt you can sprint 10K that fast.

243
00:17:38,328 --> 00:17:42,582
[breathes heavily]

244
00:17:48,171 --> 00:17:50,298
I can drive a car.

245
00:17:51,424 --> 00:17:53,384
[laughing]

246
00:17:54,135 --> 00:17:59,349
[laughing]

247
00:18:03,603 --> 00:18:05,230
And where are you going, tough guy?

248
00:18:05,313 --> 00:18:07,899
Well? Stupid son of a bitch!

249
00:18:07,982 --> 00:18:08,858
Oh!

250
00:18:09,734 --> 00:18:10,902
Fuck you!

251
00:18:14,155 --> 00:18:17,117
[henchman 1] You're going down,
asshole! [grunting]

252
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,284
Come here, fucker!

253
00:18:18,868 --> 00:18:20,537
[both grunting]

254
00:18:21,788 --> 00:18:22,747
[In-beom grunts]

255
00:18:23,248 --> 00:18:25,250
[tense music playing]

256
00:18:27,502 --> 00:18:28,628
[In-beom growls]

257
00:18:35,802 --> 00:18:37,428
[In-beom growls]

258
00:18:39,472 --> 00:18:42,225
[henchman 2] Hey! Hey!
I got you now! [groans]

259
00:18:43,226 --> 00:18:44,853
[both grunting]

260
00:18:48,106 --> 00:18:49,607
[henchman 3 gasps]

261
00:18:50,191 --> 00:18:51,234
[henchman 3 groans]

262
00:18:52,819 --> 00:18:54,112
[both grunting]

263
00:19:01,744 --> 00:19:04,414
[grunts] Fucking bastards! You fuckers!

264
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:11,087
[henchman 4 screaming in pain]

265
00:19:11,171 --> 00:19:12,422
[hair ripping]

266
00:19:12,505 --> 00:19:14,591
[screams] Ah!

267
00:19:14,674 --> 00:19:17,760
-[dull thud]
-Okay, motherfuckers, who's next?!

268
00:19:18,344 --> 00:19:20,847
[henchman 4 whimpering]

269
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:21,848
[In-beom growls]

270
00:19:24,058 --> 00:19:26,102
[sighs] They're all idiots.

271
00:19:29,063 --> 00:19:31,024
[laughing]

272
00:19:31,107 --> 00:19:33,318
[man] You weak fucking bastards.
Get the fuck up!

273
00:19:33,401 --> 00:19:34,402
Right now!

274
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,738
Get on your feet!

275
00:19:39,782 --> 00:19:40,783
[laughs]

276
00:19:53,213 --> 00:19:54,547
[grunting]

277
00:20:07,769 --> 00:20:09,646
[In-beom growls]

278
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:11,606
[In-beom groans]

279
00:20:12,857 --> 00:20:14,192
[In-beom groans]

280
00:20:14,275 --> 00:20:15,610
[In-beom growls]

281
00:20:16,819 --> 00:20:20,156
[breathes heavily]

282
00:20:22,075 --> 00:20:25,453
[In-beom breathes heavily]

283
00:20:27,872 --> 00:20:30,333
Go for it. I'll kill you.

284
00:20:31,626 --> 00:20:34,712
-[tense music builds]
-[In-beom grunting]

285
00:20:39,259 --> 00:20:42,887
[In-beom growling]

286
00:20:45,056 --> 00:20:45,932
[groaning]

287
00:20:49,018 --> 00:20:50,103
[music fades]

288
00:20:50,186 --> 00:20:51,562
[In-beom groans]

289
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,899
[both breathe heavily]

290
00:20:55,817 --> 00:20:57,860
Ugh, that's fucking great.

291
00:20:58,987 --> 00:21:01,906
[snarls, heaves]

292
00:21:04,951 --> 00:21:05,785
Hey.

293
00:21:06,411 --> 00:21:07,245
Hey.

294
00:21:08,037 --> 00:21:10,123
I thought this little bitch was weak,
but he isn't.

295
00:21:12,166 --> 00:21:14,377
But you did learn how to box
the wrong way.

296
00:21:18,089 --> 00:21:20,049
I'm gonna make cash off Kim Gun-woo.

297
00:21:22,302 --> 00:21:23,636
You can earn some too.

298
00:21:24,387 --> 00:21:25,221
You understand?

299
00:21:25,888 --> 00:21:30,852
[cackling]

300
00:21:31,436 --> 00:21:34,814
Choke on this one. [laughing]

301
00:21:34,897 --> 00:21:41,863
[laughter continues]

302
00:21:44,449 --> 00:21:45,450
[In-beom groans]

303
00:21:46,576 --> 00:21:47,702
[exhales]

304
00:22:05,970 --> 00:22:07,305
Ten… Hut!

305
00:22:07,388 --> 00:22:08,639
[exhales]

306
00:22:08,723 --> 00:22:10,975
[quiet intriguing music playing]

307
00:22:14,187 --> 00:22:16,064
Ten… hut!

308
00:22:27,241 --> 00:22:28,201
At ease.

309
00:22:30,119 --> 00:22:33,039
-At ease.
-1216 Class Marine Hong Woo-Jin.

310
00:22:33,122 --> 00:22:33,956
Ack!

311
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:38,711
This Marine is extremely proud
of our fellow junior Marines.

312
00:22:38,795 --> 00:22:40,963
Not because of the boxing title shot!

313
00:22:41,047 --> 00:22:42,840
Before Gun-woo became the champ,

314
00:22:42,924 --> 00:22:46,677
our junior Marines remained strong
and stuck together,

315
00:22:46,761 --> 00:22:48,221
which shows the true Marine spirit.

316
00:22:48,304 --> 00:22:51,766
It's the process
that I'm proudest of. Understand?

317
00:22:52,517 --> 00:22:53,351
Ack!

318
00:22:55,061 --> 00:22:55,895
[chuckles]

319
00:22:57,605 --> 00:22:59,315
Now, come here!

320
00:23:01,109 --> 00:23:04,862
[laughing] So great to see you.
How's it been?

321
00:23:04,946 --> 00:23:08,199
Wow, your face looks like
it's seen too much action.

322
00:23:08,282 --> 00:23:11,119
[laughing] You punk.

323
00:23:12,036 --> 00:23:13,913
[Mr. Moon chuckles]

324
00:23:15,623 --> 00:23:18,167
-They came up to your home?
-Yes.

325
00:23:19,127 --> 00:23:22,338
Oh. Shit, their intel
is far superior to our military.

326
00:23:22,422 --> 00:23:24,799
They brought a billion won
just for signing.

327
00:23:24,882 --> 00:23:26,509
-One billion?
-[Woo-jin] Yes.

328
00:23:26,592 --> 00:23:30,304
They offered 15 billion
if he only fought just one time.

329
00:23:30,930 --> 00:23:32,181
Just one fight.

330
00:23:33,683 --> 00:23:36,102
Wow, 15 billion won for one fight.

331
00:23:37,186 --> 00:23:38,271
[lighter clicks]

332
00:23:40,982 --> 00:23:42,608
For that huge price,

333
00:23:43,109 --> 00:23:45,445
I assume it can't only be here in Korea.

334
00:23:45,528 --> 00:23:49,240
That's right. The site says there are
over four million members worldwide.

335
00:23:49,824 --> 00:23:52,285
Four million members? How do they air it?

336
00:23:52,368 --> 00:23:54,954
Well, sir, it's on the dark web now.

337
00:23:55,663 --> 00:23:59,375
Let me explain.
So the Internet that we use, it's, uh…

338
00:23:59,459 --> 00:24:04,088
-It's like the tip of an iceberg--
-Yeah, I know it. Mm.

339
00:24:04,172 --> 00:24:06,841
All right. Dark web.

340
00:24:08,551 --> 00:24:10,720
Honestly, I only
found out about it just now.

341
00:24:10,803 --> 00:24:14,515
Okay, so they show all of these matches
on the dark web.

342
00:24:15,016 --> 00:24:17,143
And the viewers bet on the fights, right?

343
00:24:17,768 --> 00:24:18,769
That seems right.

344
00:24:19,353 --> 00:24:23,733
So… if they can get
a real champion like Gun-woo…

345
00:24:25,735 --> 00:24:26,903
Oh yeah.

346
00:24:27,737 --> 00:24:29,238
I'm sure that underground boxing world

347
00:24:29,322 --> 00:24:32,325
would be a massive powerhouse
in all sports.

348
00:24:32,408 --> 00:24:33,242
And why?

349
00:24:34,035 --> 00:24:36,829
Because just our boy alone
would hold up this league.

350
00:24:37,413 --> 00:24:39,916
Doesn't matter if it's a billion
or 15 billion won.

351
00:24:39,999 --> 00:24:43,753
They'd invest a ton of money, knowing
that in the long run, it'll only grow.

352
00:24:44,879 --> 00:24:46,047
I hear you.

353
00:24:46,547 --> 00:24:47,381
So…

354
00:24:49,509 --> 00:24:51,636
What kind of help
can I bring to the table?

355
00:24:51,719 --> 00:24:54,347
To access their website,
you need to sign up for a membership.

356
00:24:54,430 --> 00:24:55,598
It's the only way.

357
00:24:56,098 --> 00:24:58,476
And you sign up with a credit card only.

358
00:24:58,559 --> 00:25:00,436
That means personal information
can be leaked--

359
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:02,313
A mule card is a must for this.

360
00:25:03,523 --> 00:25:05,608
You're one step ahead of us
all of the time.

361
00:25:05,691 --> 00:25:07,527
[chuckles]

362
00:25:07,610 --> 00:25:09,570
-Sun-bo, hey!
-Yes?

363
00:25:10,071 --> 00:25:12,406
Uh, could you
bring over to me three mule cards?

364
00:25:12,490 --> 00:25:14,200
-[Sun-bo] Yes.
-Those fancy elite ones.

365
00:25:14,283 --> 00:25:15,326
Yes.

366
00:25:15,409 --> 00:25:16,661
That's that.

367
00:25:17,286 --> 00:25:19,747
[chuckles] Have some more coffee.

368
00:25:21,374 --> 00:25:22,208
Great.

369
00:25:24,252 --> 00:25:26,170
Here. Use them freely.

370
00:25:28,214 --> 00:25:29,048
[music fades]

371
00:25:29,131 --> 00:25:30,675
It's much appreciated, sir.

372
00:25:30,758 --> 00:25:33,344
And who's helping you
with all this right now then?

373
00:25:34,178 --> 00:25:36,556
[Woo-jin] Good question. For now,

374
00:25:37,181 --> 00:25:39,725
Gun-woo and I are all by ourselves.

375
00:25:39,809 --> 00:25:44,146
[laughing] Oh. Oh, come on.

376
00:25:44,814 --> 00:25:48,150
If they're as big as I think,
then you both are going to be outmanned.

377
00:25:48,234 --> 00:25:49,485
Do you know what I'm saying?

378
00:25:49,569 --> 00:25:50,945
Sure, it's difficult.

379
00:25:51,445 --> 00:25:53,739
But after beating Kim Myeong-gil,
we're much stronger.

380
00:25:53,823 --> 00:25:55,449
[laughs]

381
00:25:57,827 --> 00:26:00,830
I'm not so sure
that you two are that much stronger.

382
00:26:01,956 --> 00:26:03,583
It seems obvious to me.

383
00:26:04,417 --> 00:26:06,502
Why not ask me to come along and help?

384
00:26:08,504 --> 00:26:10,047
[Woo-jin] Sir, we thought about that.

385
00:26:10,798 --> 00:26:12,216
And we'd be uncomfortable.

386
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:14,552
It's way more trouble
for you and your team this time.

387
00:26:14,635 --> 00:26:16,762
Are you still Marine Hong Woo-jin?

388
00:26:16,846 --> 00:26:19,015
Yes, I'm still Marine Hong Woo-jin, sir.

389
00:26:19,765 --> 00:26:20,725
Did you forget?

390
00:26:21,767 --> 00:26:25,229
A blow to one Marine
is a blow to all Marines.

391
00:26:25,730 --> 00:26:29,942
Right? I can't sit around and do nothing
while you boys are in trouble.

392
00:26:30,026 --> 00:26:31,902
[poignant music playing]

393
00:26:33,487 --> 00:26:35,364
What would President Choi in heaven
think of me?

394
00:26:36,490 --> 00:26:38,242
I would be a big disgrace.

395
00:26:39,660 --> 00:26:41,078
That's not how I was trained.

396
00:26:42,163 --> 00:26:44,665
Being a superior has responsibilities.

397
00:26:49,170 --> 00:26:51,088
Two is better than only one.

398
00:26:51,839 --> 00:26:53,090
Add one more…

399
00:26:53,758 --> 00:26:55,343
Three is better, right?

400
00:26:58,346 --> 00:26:59,263
Take it.

401
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,475
Your superior

402
00:27:03,351 --> 00:27:04,852
is on board with you.

403
00:27:10,483 --> 00:27:12,652
[chuckles]

404
00:27:13,152 --> 00:27:15,696
No flinching! You've still got it.

405
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:17,323
[both chuckle]

406
00:27:17,406 --> 00:27:19,367
Wait. You came by yourself?

407
00:27:19,450 --> 00:27:21,577
Yes. Gun-woo's with his mother.

408
00:27:21,661 --> 00:27:24,455
Ah. You silly, naive boy.

409
00:27:24,955 --> 00:27:27,500
-Did anyone follow you here?
-[gasps]

410
00:27:28,292 --> 00:27:30,169
-[Mr. Moon] I don't believe this!
-Oh. Right.

411
00:27:30,252 --> 00:27:32,755
They came to your house to find you.
Think they'd stop at that?

412
00:27:32,838 --> 00:27:34,840
[tense music playing]

413
00:27:36,634 --> 00:27:37,927
-That your car?
-[Woo-jin] Yes.

414
00:27:38,511 --> 00:27:39,512
New plan.

415
00:27:39,595 --> 00:27:42,973
Drive around the neighborhood,
and after a few blocks, come back around.

416
00:27:43,599 --> 00:27:45,768
Let's find out
what we're up against. Copy that?

417
00:27:56,445 --> 00:27:57,446
[man] He's back.

418
00:28:05,162 --> 00:28:06,914
-Sun-bo.
-[Sun-bo] Yes?

419
00:28:07,873 --> 00:28:08,791
Get a pen.

420
00:28:09,458 --> 00:28:10,292
Yes.

421
00:28:22,930 --> 00:28:25,933
One, four, three, nine,
two, two, nine, zero.

422
00:28:26,434 --> 00:28:28,060
[music intensifies]

423
00:28:53,919 --> 00:28:55,045
Weren't we just here?

424
00:28:55,629 --> 00:28:57,006
No.

425
00:29:08,809 --> 00:29:10,770
One, four, three nine. Right?

426
00:29:10,853 --> 00:29:12,897
-The Hyundai.
-Yes.

427
00:29:14,106 --> 00:29:15,149
Where to now?

428
00:29:17,193 --> 00:29:19,236
Woo-jin. Don't look back.

429
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:21,572
I want you to keep going.
Where else have you been today?

430
00:29:22,072 --> 00:29:24,325
So first we were
at Gun-woo's mother's house.

431
00:29:24,408 --> 00:29:25,743
Now Tae-yeong's place.

432
00:29:26,327 --> 00:29:29,163
First, call Gun-woo. Get him
to take his mother somewhere new.

433
00:29:29,246 --> 00:29:31,165
We don't know
when these thugs might return.

434
00:29:31,248 --> 00:29:34,084
I'm gonna text you an address.
See if they'll follow you there.

435
00:29:34,585 --> 00:29:35,586
Then we can beat 'em up.

436
00:29:41,884 --> 00:29:42,843
[music stops]

437
00:29:43,344 --> 00:29:45,137
WOO-JIN

438
00:29:47,181 --> 00:29:48,808
-Oh, hey.
-Listen carefully.

439
00:29:48,891 --> 00:29:50,476
You have to move calmly and quickly.

440
00:29:51,060 --> 00:29:53,604
[breathes deeply] Mm-hmm.

441
00:29:53,687 --> 00:29:56,315
You must get Tae-yeong and your mother
out of that place right now.

442
00:29:56,941 --> 00:29:57,775
Why?

443
00:29:57,858 --> 00:29:59,735
Because we're being followed.

444
00:30:00,569 --> 00:30:02,988
[breathes deeply]

445
00:30:03,072 --> 00:30:05,241
You need to take Tae-yeong with you.

446
00:30:05,825 --> 00:30:07,409
Because of us, she's in trouble too.

447
00:30:08,577 --> 00:30:10,746
Mm. Mm. Got it.

448
00:30:11,914 --> 00:30:12,832
What's up with you now?

449
00:30:12,915 --> 00:30:17,795
Mr. Moon and I will find the bastard
who's been harassing and following us.

450
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:20,881
Keep your mother safe, okay?
And Tae-yeong too.

451
00:30:21,382 --> 00:30:24,093
Mm. Okay.

452
00:30:26,095 --> 00:30:27,137
And where should we go now?

453
00:30:28,264 --> 00:30:30,224
So there's Min-beom. Our best choice.

454
00:30:30,307 --> 00:30:33,185
I can't think of anyone else right now.
We need to act fast.

455
00:30:33,686 --> 00:30:35,104
Mm. On it.

456
00:30:35,187 --> 00:30:36,605
[Woo-jin] Good. Be careful.

457
00:30:36,689 --> 00:30:38,816
[somber music playing]

458
00:30:38,899 --> 00:30:41,652
[breathes deeply]

459
00:30:56,375 --> 00:30:59,712
MIN-BEOM

460
00:31:00,588 --> 00:31:02,047
[inhales]

461
00:31:06,552 --> 00:31:11,432
[outgoing call ringing]

462
00:31:13,642 --> 00:31:17,229
[electronic voice] The person
you are trying to reach is unavailable.

463
00:31:17,313 --> 00:31:18,147
Hmm.

464
00:31:19,690 --> 00:31:22,067
[breathes deeply]

465
00:31:22,151 --> 00:31:23,110
Tae-yeong.

466
00:31:25,154 --> 00:31:27,531
So I'm really, really sorry about this.

467
00:31:28,115 --> 00:31:30,242
It turns out that we've put you in danger.

468
00:31:31,577 --> 00:31:34,747
It seems like the men after us
followed us here as well.

469
00:31:36,123 --> 00:31:36,957
Oh.

470
00:31:39,418 --> 00:31:41,003
So it's dangerous for me here too?

471
00:31:42,963 --> 00:31:43,797
Yeah.

472
00:31:44,465 --> 00:31:45,841
They could be here any minute.

473
00:31:45,925 --> 00:31:47,176
I'll pack now.

474
00:31:48,218 --> 00:31:49,845
-I'm really sorry.
-[Tae-yeong] It's okay.

475
00:31:51,972 --> 00:31:52,890
[exhales]

476
00:31:52,973 --> 00:31:54,558
[So-yeon] So where are we going now?

477
00:31:55,059 --> 00:31:56,727
Uh, well…

478
00:31:57,728 --> 00:32:00,230
[exhales] Gun-woo, it's okay.
I'll find us a place to move.

479
00:32:04,485 --> 00:32:05,361
[So-yeon exhales]

480
00:32:05,444 --> 00:32:06,445
[cell phone buzzes]

481
00:32:08,447 --> 00:32:09,490
[cell phone buzzes]

482
00:32:11,492 --> 00:32:12,618
Hello?

483
00:32:12,701 --> 00:32:16,121
Gun-woo? Hello, this is Cho Won-yeong.
I'm President Hong's assistant.

484
00:32:16,664 --> 00:32:18,832
Oh! Yes, hi there.

485
00:32:18,916 --> 00:32:21,043
Unfortunately, President Hong is
in an important meeting

486
00:32:21,126 --> 00:32:22,962
with dignitaries from overseas.

487
00:32:23,045 --> 00:32:25,130
But he asked me to phone you right away.

488
00:32:25,631 --> 00:32:27,508
What message can I pass on?

489
00:32:28,217 --> 00:32:29,802
It's a very private matter.

490
00:32:30,302 --> 00:32:32,972
Whatever you say will remain private.
I promise that.

491
00:32:34,139 --> 00:32:35,432
My loved ones

492
00:32:36,308 --> 00:32:37,559
are in big trouble.

493
00:32:39,728 --> 00:32:40,813
My mother

494
00:32:41,522 --> 00:32:43,691
really needs a safe place
to stay right now.

495
00:32:44,817 --> 00:32:47,528
You can bring your mother
right away to our building, Mr. Kim.

496
00:32:47,611 --> 00:32:51,365
We'll make sure to have guards on standby.
Is there anything else I can do for you?

497
00:32:51,448 --> 00:32:53,200
Okay. Well, actually…

498
00:32:53,742 --> 00:32:57,037
So if it's at all possible,
a motor… motorcycle would help.

499
00:32:57,997 --> 00:33:01,125
I have to save Woo-jin, and traffic
at this time makes that harder.

500
00:33:02,126 --> 00:33:04,670
[Won-yeong] We can do that.
Any particular type of motorcycle?

501
00:33:04,753 --> 00:33:07,881
Uh, a fast one.
It doesn't matter. I can ride anything.

502
00:33:08,382 --> 00:33:10,801
[Won-yeong] Then you'll have
the fastest one at our disposal.

503
00:33:11,510 --> 00:33:12,761
I appreciate it.

504
00:33:16,890 --> 00:33:17,891
[groans]

505
00:33:17,975 --> 00:33:21,603
[breathing deeply]

506
00:33:23,772 --> 00:33:25,774
[suspenseful music playing]

507
00:33:31,655 --> 00:33:32,614
[sighs]

508
00:33:44,418 --> 00:33:46,712
-Tell me what's up.
-Yeah…

509
00:33:46,795 --> 00:33:47,629
What?

510
00:33:50,174 --> 00:33:51,884
-They're on the run.
-What?

511
00:33:51,967 --> 00:33:53,469
They're all moving out right now.

512
00:33:53,552 --> 00:33:54,553
Who is?

513
00:33:54,636 --> 00:33:57,639
Gun-woo, his mom,
and that chick in the wheelchair.

514
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,600
What do we do?

515
00:34:02,144 --> 00:34:03,270
[outgoing call ringing]

516
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:05,814
What?

517
